column3:
{pageend:Welcome to the Contest Hall!}
This is the reception counter for linked
{pageend:Super Contest Shows.}
You and your friends may enter your Pokémon in
the same Super Contest Show together.

Hi! This is the registration counter for
{pageend:practice sessions.}
Here you can take Contest Show lessons!

The Visual Evaluation will be based on the
Pokémon’s conditions and the spectacle of
{pageend:its customized Ball Capsule.}
There are five types of conditions: Coolness,
{pageend:Beauty, Cuteness, Cleverness, and Toughness.}
You can raise each of these by giving your
{pageend:Pokémon Poffins!}
Customize your Capsule Decoration by placing
Stickers onto Ball Capsules. You can access them
{pageend:through the X menu or by using a PC.}
Different Stickers pair well with different contest
shows, so try out a variety of them!

The Dance Evaluation is based on your
{pageend:rhythm skills!}
Push the button with the right timing as notes
{pageend:move along with the music.}
Scores for each note are divided into categories:
{pageend:Too Fast/Slow, Nice, Great, and Brilliant!}
The better your timing, the more your Heart
Gauge will fill, and when it fills up completely,
you’ll get a <color=#F01E1EFF>♥</color>{pageend:!}
A performance that earns a lot of <color=#F01E1EFF>♥</color>s is definitely
a brilliant one! And that’ll be sure to send your
{pageend:Dance Evaluation score sky high, too!}
Collecting <color=#F01E1EFF>♥</color>s will also raise the Hype Meter
shared by all four performers, pumping up the
{pageend:audience into a frenzy!}
Put on successful shows to earn hall points,
and you can gradually upgrade the stage into
something truly magnificent!

