The Move Evaluation is based on a Pokémon’s
Contest Move, which the Pokémon can only use
{pageend:once during the performance!}
Contest Moves can have a variety of effects
{pageend:that will help with the Dance Evaluation.}
Choose the move you’d like in advance at the
reception desk, then use your Contest Move
{pageend:when you feel like the moment is right!}
Based on the success of your move, you may
receive <color=#F01E1EFF>♥</color>{pageend:s from the audience!}
Also, if you coordinate with other performers and
use Contest Moves in succession, you can create
a Move Chain! Pull it off, and you’ll get more
<color=#F01E1EFF>♥</color>{pageend:s than if you’d just used a move on your own.}
If you create a Move Chain with moves that have
the same type, you’ll get even more <color=#F01E1EFF>♥</color>{pageend:s.}
The key to success is figuring out the perfect
time to use your Contest Move!

There are four different ranks of Link Contest
{pageend:Shows: Normal, Great, Ultra, and Master.}
The difficulty level increases as you approach
{pageend:Master Rank.}
For Link Contest Shows, all ranks are playable
right from the start!

